40:43.203 --> 40:45.686
but for my first prototype
in grad school ‐‐

40:45.686 --> 40:48.729
the CO2 scrubber.

40:48.729 --> 40:51.932
That's how Spano found me.

40:51.932 --> 40:56.016
But I needed 200 grand,
and Elena gave it to me.

40:56.016 --> 40:57.858
‐Would you rather sit
in the photo?

40:57.858 --> 41:01.221
‐I'd rather stand.
‐Okay. We're almost done.

41:01.221 --> 41:04.024
‐It disgusted me
having to ask her.

41:04.024 --> 41:05.746
There she was,
earning all this money

41:05.746 --> 41:08.308
for doing absolutely nothing,
just standing there,

41:08.308 --> 41:12.272
and I was trying
to build something.

41:14.715 --> 41:16.877
I resented her.

41:16.877 --> 41:20.120
‐Okay, you can open your eyes.

41:20.120 --> 41:22.482
‐Over time,
I've come to admire her.

41:22.482 --> 41:26.286
I mean, it can't have been easy
just...standing there

41:26.286 --> 41:28.008
